{
  "stem": "11771.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When he told my mother he's going to be in the-- in the shul-- in the picture, I'll show you-- I took mine brother.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother suggest not to go to the shul, but to run away to the farm where I was in hiding before.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I took my mother-- she gives me a challah, I remember, on the way.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I took my brother, and we run-- start to run to Horbaczewski, to the farm where I was in hiding before.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was about five kilometer from-- from the town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But as soon as we came-- we're getting out of borders of the town-- the Lithuanian was blocking.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they turned us-- us back to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I came into the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I find my father.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And at the-- in one hour, the shul was packed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And maybe I would say by 900 people, by 1,000 people, with the children, with-- with everything, with all the-- everybody was-- it was-- could carry on from their house into the shul.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I find there also my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She's still in there, with her son, and her husband, and the other mother's sister, with her husband.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And-- and we're sitting down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it's panic-- the yelling and the screaming, and-- and-- and-- and-- and the crying from the children, from all over-- was so terrible.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And everybody were trying to find a place even to sit down.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we were sitting close to each other-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] sitting like this for two hours.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You know, people need to do their need for what they need to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And people start to yell and to step on each other.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
